Overview

This phase of the vulnerability management process focused on identifying web application misconfigurations, exposed services, and exploitable vulnerabilities using industry-standard tools in a controlled lab environment.

Objective

To perform automated web server scanning in order to identify:
                                                              Outdated software versions
                                                              Dangerous files and directories
                                                              Security misconfigurations
                                                              Missing HTTP security headers
 nikto -h http://<target_ip>
 Nikto performs over 6,000 tests including:
Server version disclosure
Default credentials
Insecure HTTP methods
Directory indexing
Known vulnerable scripts
SSL configuration issues

 | Finding                    | Risk Level | Description                  |
| -------------------------- | ---------- | ---------------------------- |
| Outdated Apache Version    | High       | Vulnerable to known CVEs     |
| Directory Indexing Enabled | Medium     | Sensitive files exposed      |
| Missing Security Headers   | Medium     | Increased XSS risk           |
| Exposed Admin Page         | High       | Potential brute-force target |


