                 Vulnerability & Misconfiguration Analysis
| # | Issue                          | Description                                | Risk Impact                                                    | Severity | Remediation                                                           |
| - | ------------------------------ | ------------------------------------------ | -------------------------------------------------------------- | -------- | --------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| 1 | Server Version Disclosure      | Server header reveals `openresty/1.27.1.2` | Enables attackers to search for known CVEs and tailor exploits | Medium   | Disable server tokens and hide version banners (`server_tokens off;`) |
| 2 | Private/Internal IP Disclosure | IP address exposed in server header        | Reveals backend architecture; assists reconnaissance           | Medium   | Sanitize HTTP response headers before sending to clients              |
| 3 | Missing X-Frame-Options        | Anti-clickjacking header not set           | Website can be embedded in malicious iframe                    | Medium   | Add `X-Frame-Options: DENY` or `SAMEORIGIN`                           |
| 4 | Missing HSTS Header            | Strict-Transport-Security not defined      | Vulnerable to SSL stripping and downgrade attacks              | High     | Add `Strict-Transport-Security: max-age=31536000; includeSubDomains`  |
| 5 | Missing X-Content-Type-Options | MIME sniffing protection absent            | Browser may execute malicious content incorrectly              | Medium   | Add `X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff`                                 |
